{"id":19972,"title":"Using fluorescence correlation spectroscopy (FCS) for IFN-g detection: a preliminary study.","abstract":"Nowadays, enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) based detection of Mycobacterium tuberculosis (M. tuberculosis) antigen triggered interferon-gamma (IFN-g) secretion by blood T cells displays an improved diagnostic value for M. tuberculosis infection. Applications of fluorescence correlation spectroscopy (FCS) have been explored in various subfields of medicine and molecular biology, including detection of a certain biomarker in liquid instead of ELISA. Here, we present a preliminary study of detecting IFN-g using FCS-based technique. ","date":"2014-05-27","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24685834","annotations":[{"name":"Biomarker","weight":0.950911,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biomarker"},{"name":"Tuberculosis","weight":0.895066,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuberculosis"},{"name":"ELISA","weight":0.881428,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ELISA"},{"name":"Mycobacterium tuberculosis","weight":0.877036,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mycobacterium_tuberculosis"},{"name":"Molecular biology","weight":0.829773,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Molecular_biology"},{"name":"Cell (biology)","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_(biology)"},{"name":"Secretion","weight":0.786341,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Secretion"},{"name":"Antigen","weight":0.785202,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antigen"},{"name":"Blood","weight":0.783378,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blood"},{"name":"Medicine","weight":0.782137,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicine"},{"name":"T cell","weight":0.757147,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/T_cell"},{"name":"Biology","weight":0.756238,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biology"},{"name":"Fluorescence","weight":0.718674,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluorescence"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.660386,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Mycobacterium","weight":0.646519,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mycobacterium"},{"name":"Molecule","weight":0.591436,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Molecule"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.47851,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Spectroscopy","weight":0.414979,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spectroscopy"},{"name":"Assay","weight":0.358068,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Assay"},{"name":"Correlation and dependence","weight":0.259972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Correlation_and_dependence"},{"name":"Liquid","weight":0.089122,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liquid"},{"name":"Receptor (biochemistry)","weight":0.0318009,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Receptor_(biochemistry)"},{"name":"Fluorescence correlation spectroscopy","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluorescence_correlation_spectroscopy"},{"name":"Two-dimensional nuclear magnetic resonance spectroscopy","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Two-dimensional_nuclear_magnetic_resonance_spectroscopy"}]}
